reference:
LZF Functions LZF
&reftitle.intro;
LZF is a very fast compression algorithm, ideal for saving space with only slight speed cost. It can be optimized for speed or space in compilation time.
&reftitle.install;
LZF is currently available through PECL (http://pecl.php.net/lzf). To install LZF extension all you need to do is:
gunzip lzf-xxx.tgz tar -xvf lzf-xxx.tar cd lzf-xxx phpize ./configure && make && make install
You can pass --enable-lzf-better-compression to optimize lzf for space rather then speed.
